<h2 id="precursor">Precursor to the Revolution</h2>
<p>Written on October 15, 1966, the Black Panther Party Ten-Point Program outlines a clear set of demands aimed at achieving justice, equality, and self-determination for Black communities. Framed as a response to systemic racism and economic exploitation, the document calls for structural change and community empowerment through education, housing, employment, and protection from state violence.</p>

<h2 id="section1">Section 1 – What We Want</h2>
<p>1. We want freedom. We want power to determine the destiny of our Black Community.</p>
<p>2. We want full employment for our people.</p>
<p>3. We want an end to the robbery by the white man of our Black Community.</p>
<p>4. We want decent housing, fit for shelter of human beings.</p>
<p>5. We want education for our people that exposes the true nature of this decadent American society.</p>

<h2 id="section2">Section 2 – What We Believe</h2>
<p>We believe that black people will not be free until we are able to determine our destiny.</p>
<p>We believe that the federal government is responsible and obligated to give every man employment or a guaranteed income.</p>
<p>We believe in an educational system that will give to our people a knowledge of self.</p>

<h2 id="section3">Section 3 – Rules of the Black Panther Party</h2>
<p>Every member of the Black Panther Party must abide by these rules as functional members of this party.</p>
<p>1. No party member can have narcotics or weed in his possession while doing party work.</p>
<p>2. No party member can be drunk while doing daily party work.</p>
<p>3. No party member will use, point, or fire a weapon of any kind unnecessarily or accidentally at anyone.</p>

<h2 id="section4">Section 4 - 8 Points of Attention</h2>
<p>Speak politely.</p>
<p>Pay fairly for what you buy.</p>
<p>Return everything you borrow.</p>
<p>Pay for anything you damage.</p>

<h2 id="section5">Section 5 – 3 Main Rules of Discipline</h2>
<p>Obey orders in all your actions.</p>
<p>Do not take a single needle or piece of thread from the poor and oppressed masses.</p>
<p>Turn in everything captured from the attacking enemy.</p>

